(2, 1, 1, 1, 'Apple Airpods', 'It\'s helpful to specify which AirPods model you\'re interested in, as specifications vary. However, I can provide you with general information and point you to official Apple resources.', '<p>Here are detailed specifications for **Apple AirPods** (based on the latest models available as of October 2023, including AirPods 2nd Gen, AirPods 3rd Gen, and AirPods Pro 2nd Gen):</p>\r\n<p>### **Apple AirPods (2nd Generation)**</p>\r\n<p>- **Dimensions**:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 1.59 x 0.65 x 0.71 inches (40.5 x 16.5 x 18.0 mm)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 2.11 x 1.74 x 0.84 inches (53.5 x 44.3 x 21.3 mm)</p>\r\n<p>- **Weight**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 0.14 oz (4 g) each</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 1.34 oz (38 g)</p>\r\n<p>- **Chip**: Apple H1 Headphone Chip</p>\r\n<p>- **Connectivity**: Bluetooth 5.0</p>\r\n<p>- **Battery Life**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 5 hours of listening time (on a single charge)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 3 hours of talk time (on a single charge)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Over 24 hours of total listening time with the charging case</p>\r\n<p>- **Charging**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Wireless Charging Case (optional)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Lightning connector for wired charging</p>\r\n<p>- **Audio Features**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Dual beamforming microphones</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Dual optical sensors</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Accelerometer for motion detection</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Voice detection with accelerometer</p>\r\n<p>- **Controls**: Double-tap to play, skip, or answer calls</p>\r\n<p>- **Compatibility**: Works with iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, Mac, and Apple TV</p>\r\n<p>- **Water Resistance**: No official IP rating (sweat and water-resistant, but not waterproof)</p>\r\n<p>- **Colors**: White</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>### **Apple AirPods (3rd Generation)**</p>\r\n<p>- **Dimensions**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 1.21 x 0.76 x 0.72 inches (30.79 x 18.26 x 19.21 mm)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 1.83 x 2.14 x 0.84 inches (46.40 x 54.40 x 21.38 mm)</p>\r\n<p>- **Weight**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 0.15 oz (4.28 g) each</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 1.34 oz (37.91 g)</p>\r\n<p>- **Chip**: Apple H1 Headphone Chip</p>\r\n<p>- **Connectivity**: Bluetooth 5.0</p>\r\n<p>- **Battery Life**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 6 hours of listening time (on a single charge)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 4 hours of talk time (on a single charge)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 30 hours of total listening time with the charging case</p>\r\n<p>- **Charging**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- MagSafe Charging Case (supports wireless charging)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Lightning connector for wired charging</p>\r\n<p>- **Audio Features**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Adaptive EQ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Spatial Audio with dynamic head tracking</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Sweat and water-resistant (IPX4 rating)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Force sensor controls for media playback and calls</p>\r\n<p>- **Controls**: Press force sensor to play, pause, skip, or answer calls</p>\r\n<p>- **Compatibility**: Works with iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, Mac, and Apple TV</p>\r\n<p>- **Colors**: White</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>### **Apple AirPods Pro (2nd Generation)**</p>\r\n<p>- **Dimensions**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 1.22 x 0.86 x 0.94 inches (30.9 x 21.8 x 24.0 mm)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 1.78 x 2.39 x 0.85 inches (45.2 x 60.6 x 21.7 mm)</p>\r\n<p>- **Weight**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- AirPods: 0.19 oz (5.3 g) each</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Charging Case: 1.79 oz (50.8 g)</p>\r\n<p>- **Chip**: Apple H2 Headphone Chip</p>\r\n<p>- **Connectivity**: Bluetooth 5.3</p>\r\n<p>- **Battery Life**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 6 hours of listening time (on a single charge with Active Noise Cancellation enabled)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 4.5 hours of talk time (on a single charge)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Up to 30 hours of total listening time with the charging case</p>\r\n<p>- **Charging**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- MagSafe Charging Case (supports wireless charging)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- USB-C connector for wired charging</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Precision Finding with U1 chip for locating the case</p>\r\n<p>- **Audio Features**:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Active Noise Cancellation (ANC) and Transparency mode</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Adaptive Audio (dynamic blending of ANC and Transparency)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Personalized Spatial Audio with dynamic head tracking</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Adaptive EQ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Sweat and water-resistant (IPX4 rating)</p>\r\n<p>- **Controls**: Force sensor for media playback, calls, and switching between ANC/Transparency modes</p>\r\n<p>- **Compatibility**: Works with iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, Mac, and Apple TV</p>\r\n<p>- **Colors**: White</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>### **Additional Features (Across All Models)**:</p>\r\n<p>- **Find My Support**: Locate lost AirPods using the Find My app.</p>\r\n<p>- **Automatic Switching**: Seamlessly switch between Apple devices signed in to the same iCloud account.</p>\r\n<p>- **Siri Integration**: Hands-free \"Hey Siri\" support.</p>\r\n<p>- **Customizable Fit**: AirPods Pro come with silicone ear tips in multiple sizes for a secure fit.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>These specifications are based on the latest models available as of October 2023. Let me know if you\'d like more details!</p>\r\n', 700, '10001', 'Active'),
(3, 1, 4, 4, 'Toyota Camry 2024', 'The 2024 Toyota Camry remains a practical and dependable choice for those seeking a comfortable and efficient midsize sedan. However, potential buyers should be aware of the upcoming 2025 redesign.', '<p>Here are the detailed specifications for the <strong>2024 Toyota Camry</strong>, covering its engine options, dimensions, performance, safety features, and technology.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Engine &amp; Performance</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Base Engine</strong>: 2.5L 4-cylinder, producing <strong>202-203 hp</strong> and <strong>184-186 lb-ft torque</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>V6 Engine (TRD, XSE, XLE trims)</strong>: 3.5L V6, delivering <strong>301 hp</strong> and <strong>267 lb-ft torque</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Transmission</strong>: 8-speed automatic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Drivetrain Options</strong>: Front-Wheel Drive (FWD) or All-Wheel Drive (AWD).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Fuel Efficiency</strong>:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>4-cylinder models: <strong>28 MPG city / 39 MPG highway (FWD)</strong>, <strong>25 MPG city / 34 MPG highway (AWD)</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>V6 models: <strong>22 MPG city / 31 MPG highway</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Dimensions</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Overall Length</strong>: 192.1 inches.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Width</strong>: 72 inches.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Height</strong>: 57.1 inches.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wheelbase</strong>: 111 inches.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ground Clearance</strong>: 6 inches.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Curb Weight</strong>: 3,310 - 3,590 lbs (varies by trim &amp; drivetrain).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Interior &amp; Cargo</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Seating Capacity</strong>: 5 passengers.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Passenger Volume</strong>: 100 cubic feet.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cargo (Trunk) Volume</strong>: 15 cubic feet.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Available Features</strong>: Heated &amp; ventilated front seats, dual-zone climate control, leather upholstery (higher trims), power-adjustable seats.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Safety &amp; Driver Assistance</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Standard Toyota Safety Sense 2.5+</strong>, including:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lane Departure Warning with Steering Assist</li>\r\n<li>Pre-Collision System with Pedestrian Detection</li>\r\n<li>Adaptive Cruise Control</li>\r\n<li>Blind Spot Monitoring (optional on lower trims, standard on higher ones)</li>\r\n<li>Rear Cross-Traffic Alert</li>\r\n<li>Automatic Emergency Braking</li>\r\n<li>Backup Camera</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Technology &amp; Infotainment</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Standard</strong>: 7-inch or 9-inch touchscreen with Apple CarPlay &amp; Android Auto.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Available</strong>: Wireless charging, premium JBL sound system, head-up display, Wi-Fi hotspot.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Navigation System</strong>: Standard on higher trims.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Trim Levels &amp; Pricing</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Base LE</strong>: $26,420 (FWD), $27,820 (AWD)</li>\r\n<li><strong>SE</strong>: $27,960 (FWD), $29,360 (AWD)</li>\r\n<li><strong>XLE</strong>: $31,170 (FWD), $32,570 (AWD)</li>\r\n<li><strong>XSE</strong>: $31,720 (FWD), $33,120 (AWD)</li>\r\n<li><strong>TRD V6</strong>: $33,485 (FWD only)</li>\r\n<li><strong>XLE V6</strong>: $36,295 (FWD only)</li>\r\n<li><strong>XSE V6</strong>: $36,845 (FWD only)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Would you like more details on a specific trim? Let me know!<br><br>(Sources: <a href=\"https://www.kbb.com/\" target=\"_self\">Kelley Blue Book</a> (<a href=\"https://www.kbb.com/toyota/camry/2024/specs/\" target=\"_self\">2024 Toyota Camry Specs &amp; Feature Comparisons | Kelley Blue Book</a>), <a href=\"https://www.cars.com/\" target=\"_self\">Cars.com</a> (<a href=\"https://www.cars.com/research/toyota-camry-2024/specs/440181/\" target=\"_self\">2024 Toyota Camry Specs, Dimensions &amp; Colors | Cars.com</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.cars.com/research/toyota-camry-2024/trims/\" target=\"_self\">2024 Toyota Camry Trim Levels &amp; Configurations | Cars.com</a>))</p>\r\n', 190000, '10002', 'Active'),
(4, 1, 5, 8, 'Chelsea Boots', 'Chelsea boots are close-fitting, ankle-high boots with elastic side panels, typically made of leather, and featuring a rounded toe with a low heel. Their defining characteristic is the elastic gusset, which allows for easy on and off without laces or zippers, while providing a snug and comfortable fit. They often incorporate a pull tab at the back for added convenience and a durable sole, making them versatile for both casual and semi-formal wear.', '<h3><strong>Complete Specifications for Chelsea Boots</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Design &amp; Features</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Elastic Side Panels</strong>: These allow easy slip-on wear without laces or buckles.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ankle Height</strong>: Typically reaches just above the ankle, providing a snug fit.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Toe Shape</strong>: Usually rounded or slightly pointed for a sleek silhouette.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pull Tab</strong>: A loop at the back to help in slipping the boots on.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Low Heel</strong>: Standard Chelsea boots have a small stacked heel for stability and elegance. Some styles include higher heels for a more sophisticated look.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sole Type</strong>: Generally thin and sleek for a formal appearance, but some versions have chunky soles for a modern, rugged style.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Materials Used</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Leather</strong>: Full-grain and top-grain leather for durability, water resistance, and a polished look.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Suede</strong>: Soft, textured material that gives a more casual aesthetic. Requires extra care.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Synthetic Leather</strong>: Vegan-friendly options mimic the look of real leather.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rubber Outsole</strong>: Provides grip and durability for all-weather conditions (<a href=\"https://nicksboots.com/blog/post/chelsea-work-boots/\" target=\"_self\">A Comprehensive Guide To Chelsea Boots</a>) (<a href=\"https://bestwalkingfeet.com/what-is-chelsea-boot/\" target=\"_self\">What is a Chelsea Boot? - Best Walking Feet</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Styles &amp; Variations</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Classic Leather Chelsea Boots</strong>: Suitable for formal and casual wear.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Suede Chelsea Boots</strong>: Lighter and more relaxed, ideal for casual outfits.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chunky Chelsea Boots</strong>: Features a thick sole for a rugged and contemporary style.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Patent Leather Chelsea Boots</strong>: High-shine boots ideal for dressy occasions.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Winter Chelsea Boots</strong>: Equipped with insulation, waterproofing, and slip-resistant soles (<a href=\"https://bestwalkingfeet.com/what-is-chelsea-boot/\" target=\"_self\">What is a Chelsea Boot? - Best Walking Feet</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>4. Comfort &amp; Fit</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Chelsea boots provide a snug but comfortable fit due to the elastic side panels.</li>\r\n<li>The low heel makes them suitable for all-day wear.</li>\r\n<li>Some models offer cushioned insoles for added comfort.</li>\r\n<li>Available in narrow, standard, and wide fits to accommodate different foot shapes (<a href=\"https://stylewhirl.com/what-is-a-chelsea-boots/\" target=\"_self\">What is a Chelsea Boot? The Ultimate Guide to This Stylish Footwear - StyleWhirl</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>5. Styling &amp; Versatility</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Casual Look</strong>: Pair with jeans and a t-shirt for a laid-back style.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Smart Casual</strong>: Works well with chinos or tailored trousers and a blazer.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Formal Wear</strong>: Leather Chelsea boots can complement suits for a polished appearance.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Seasonal Styling</strong>: Suitable for autumn and winter, with some waterproof versions available for wet conditions (<a href=\"https://bespokeunit.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/What-Is-A-Chelsea-Boot-Bespoke-Unit.pdf\" target=\"_self\">What Is A Chelsea Boot copy</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>6. Popular Brands</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dr. Martens</strong> – Known for rugged, durable Chelsea boots.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Clarks</strong> – Classic and comfortable everyday wear.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Frye</strong> – High-end craftsmanship and premium materials.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Timberland</strong> – Offers waterproof and work-friendly variations (<a href=\"https://stylewhirl.com/what-is-a-chelsea-boots/\" target=\"_self\">What is a Chelsea Boot? The Ultimate Guide to This Stylish Footwear - StyleWhirl</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>7. Care &amp; Maintenance</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Leather Boots</strong>: Clean and condition regularly with leather polish.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Suede Boots</strong>: Use a suede brush and protective spray to maintain texture.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Waterproofing</strong>: Apply protective sprays to extend the boots\' lifespan (<a href=\"https://bestwalkingfeet.com/what-is-chelsea-boot/\" target=\"_self\">What is a Chelsea Boot? - Best Walking Feet</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Chelsea boots remain one of the most versatile and stylish footwear choices, combining practicality with elegance. Whether you prefer classic leather, casual suede, or modern chunky designs, they are a timeless investment.</p>\r\n', 190, '10003', 'Inactive'),
(5, 1, 5, 8, 'Converse Sneekers', 'Converse shoes, particularly the iconic Chuck Taylor All Stars, are low or high-top canvas sneakers featuring a rubber sole and toe cap, a distinctive star logo, and lace-up closure. 1  They are known for their simple, classic design, durable construction, and versatile style, suitable for casual wear and various subcultures. Typically made with a canvas upper and a vulcanized rubber sole, they offer minimal arch support and a flexible, comfortable fit, though variations in materials and designs exist for different models and collaborations.', '<h3><strong>Full Specifications of Converse Shoes (2024)</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Materials &amp; Construction</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Upper</strong>: Primarily canvas (lightweight, breathable, and durable), though some models feature leather or suede.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sole</strong>: Thick rubber for durability and grip, with some models offering slimmer soles or additional padding.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Toe Cap</strong>: Rubber for extra protection, sometimes made of leather for premium designs.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lining</strong>: Canvas or synthetic for breathability.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Insole</strong>: Basic cushioned insole for comfort, with premium models featuring memory foam or cork footbeds.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Stitching</strong>: Durable stitching with reinforced seams for longevity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Types of Converse Shoes</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Chuck Taylor All Star</strong> (Classic high-top and low-top)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chuck 70</strong> (Premium version with thicker canvas and enhanced cushioning)</li>\r\n<li><strong>One Star</strong> (Skate-inspired with suede or leather options)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Jack Purcell</strong> (Higher-end, featuring a thicker sole and better arch support)</li>\r\n<li><strong>CONS</strong> (Skateboarding line with added traction, memory foam liner, and padded tongue)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Graphic Collections</strong> (Special designs in collaboration with artists and brands)</li>\r\n<li><strong>John Varvatos Collection</strong> (Luxury designs with rock-inspired aesthetics)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Color Variations</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Classic Colors</strong>: White, black, navy blue, gray, red, pink, beige (optical white &amp; natural white).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Seasonal Colors</strong>: Fresh Colors collection, offering new shades each season.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Distressed Look</strong>: Washed Canvas series for a vintage aesthetic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Limited Editions</strong>: Special collaborations with brands like DC Comics, Andy Warhol, and The Simpsons.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>4. Comfort &amp; Features</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cushioning</strong>: Some models include extra padding, particularly the Jack Purcell and CONS lines.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Breathability</strong>: Canvas upper ensures good air circulation.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Traction</strong>: Rubber outsole provides decent grip, but classic models may not be ideal for wet surfaces.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: Converse shoes are generally flat; models like Jack Purcell offer better arch support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>5. Manufacturing Process</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The <strong>canvas upper</strong> is cut and stitched together.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rubber soles</strong> are molded and attached using strong adhesives.</li>\r\n<li>The <strong>toe cap</strong> is added for durability.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Dyeing &amp; Printing</strong>: Logos and patterns are applied using fade-resistant dyes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>6. Price &amp; Availability</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Classic Converse models start at around <strong>$55-$75</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Premium lines (Chuck 70, Jack Purcell) range from <strong>$80-$120</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Special edition collaborations and leather models can cost <strong>$100-$200+</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Converse shoes remain a timeless, stylish, and versatile footwear choice for casual wear, skateboarding, and even high-fashion collaborations  (<a href=\"https://whattheshoes.com/what-are-converse-shoes-made-of/\" target=\"_self\">What Are Converse Shoes Made Of? (Answers Revealed) – What The Shoes</a>) (<a href=\"https://oureverydaylife.com/types-of-converse-12228161.html\" target=\"_self\">Types of Converse | Our Everyday Life</a>) (<a href=\"https://whattheshoes.com/how-do-they-make-converse-shoes/\" target=\"_self\">How Do They Make Converse Shoes? A Comprehensive Guide – What The Shoes</a>).</p>\r\n', 450, '10004', 'Active'),
(6, 1, 2, 9, 'Leather Couche', 'Leather couches are upholstered furniture pieces featuring frames typically constructed from hardwood, with cushioning made of foam or down, and a surface covering of genuine or faux leather. They prioritize durability, comfort, and a luxurious aesthetic, offering a variety of styles from classic to modern. Leather types range from full-grain to bonded, each with varying degrees of quality and texture, and may include features like tufting, reclining mechanisms, or modular configurations. Regular maintenance, such as conditioning, is essential to preserve the leather\'s appearance and longevity.', '<h3><strong>Leather Couch Specifications: Full Details</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Types of Leather Used in Couches</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Full-Grain Leather</strong>: The highest quality leather, retaining the natural grain. It is extremely durable, ages beautifully, and develops a patina over time. However, it is expensive and requires careful maintenance to prevent scratches and damage from temperature fluctuations.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Top-Grain Leather</strong>: Slightly lower quality than full-grain but still durable. It has been sanded to remove imperfections and often has a protective coating to resist stains and fading.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Split Leather</strong>: Comes from the lower layers of the hide. It is less durable than top-grain and full-grain leather but is more affordable. Variants include <strong>suede</strong> (soft, fuzzy texture) and <strong>bicast leather</strong> (polyurethane-coated for a glossy finish).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Genuine Leather</strong>: A lower grade leather made from leftover hide layers. It is treated to mimic the look of higher-quality leather but is less durable.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bonded Leather</strong>: A mix of leather scraps and synthetic materials bonded together with adhesives. It is the least expensive but also the least durable.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Synthetic Leather (PU &amp; PVC Leather)</strong>: Made from polyurethane or polyvinyl chloride. It is cost-effective, easy to clean, and available in multiple styles but lacks the longevity of real leather.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>(Sources: HomeDecorBliss, Rolford Leather, Cigno Leather)</p>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Couch Frame &amp; Suspension</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Frame Materials</strong>: Hardwood frames (oak, maple, birch) are the most durable. Plywood or engineered wood frames are more affordable but less sturdy.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Spring Systems</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Eight-Way Hand-Tied Springs</strong>: High-end, hand-secured springs for maximum comfort and longevity.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sinuous Springs</strong>: S-shaped steel springs, common in mid-range leather sofas, offer good support.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Web Suspension</strong>: A less durable system using bands of webbing, often combined with springs for reinforcement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>(Source: Club Furniture)</p>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Cushioning &amp; Filling</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Down &amp; Feathers</strong>: Soft and luxurious but requires maintenance to prevent flattening.</li>\r\n<li><strong>High-Density Foam</strong>: Most common, provides firm support with moderate durability.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Memory Foam</strong>: Offers contouring comfort but is more expensive.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pocketed Coils</strong>: Springs encased in foam, offering bounce and longevity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>(Source: Club Furniture)</p>\r\n<h4><strong>4. Maintenance &amp; Care</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Avoid direct sunlight to prevent fading.</li>\r\n<li>Clean with a soft cloth, mild soap, and water (avoid harsh chemicals).</li>\r\n<li>Condition full-grain and top-grain leather periodically.</li>\r\n<li>Keep away from moisture and spills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>(Source: Rolford Leather, Cigno Leather)</p>\r\n<p>Would you like recommendations for specific brands or models?</p>\r\n', 12000, '10005', 'Active'),
(8, 1, 7, 3, 'Smart Samsung Refrigerator', 'Samsungs refrigerators offer a range of models, from basic top-freezers to advanced French door and side-by-side units, typically featuring digital inverter compressors for energy efficiency and quiet operation. They often include features like flexible storage options, adjustable shelves, humidity-controlled crispers, and ice/water dispensers. Higher-end models may incorporate smart technology, such as Wi-Fi connectivity, touchscreen displays, and internal cameras, alongside advanced cooling systems like triple or quad cooling to maintain optimal temperature and humidity levels.', '<p></p>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Bespoke 4-Door Flex Refrigerator with AI Family Hub+</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>AI Features:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Internal AI camera identifies up to 33 different food items.</li>\r\n<li>Tracks expiration dates and sends notifications.</li>\r\n<li>Suggests recipes based on stored ingredients and dietary preferences.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Display &amp; Smart Features:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>32-inch touchscreen powered by Tizen OS.</li>\r\n<li>Supports YouTube, TikTok, Samsung Food, and Samsung Health.</li>\r\n<li>SmartThings integration for smart home control.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cooling &amp; Storage:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Flexible storage compartments.</li>\r\n<li>Customizable interior shelving.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Energy Efficiency:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>AI-powered inverter compressor for better cooling and lower energy consumption.</li>\r\n<li>Estimated energy savings of up to 10% (<a href=\"https://www.sammobile.com/news/samsung-ai-family-hub-plus-refrigerator-32-inch-screen-camera-ai/\" target=\"_self\">Samsung unveils AI Family Hub+ Refrigerator with 32-inch screen, camera - SamMobile</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.t3.com/news/new-samsung-fridge-uses-ai-to-tell-you-whats-inside-and-when-its-going-out-of-date\" target=\"_self\">New Samsung fridge uses AI to tell you what\'s inside and when it\'s going out of date | T3</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Samsung 809L Family Hub™ AI Refrigerator</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 809 liters.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Technology:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>AI Inverter Compressor with 20-year warranty.</li>\r\n<li>Operates at noise levels below 35 dB.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Smart Connectivity:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wi-Fi-enabled remote monitoring.</li>\r\n<li>AI Vision Inside for food tracking and expiration alerts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Design:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Available in Clean Charcoal + Stainless Steel finish (<a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/in/samsung-launches-three-new-refrigerators-featuring-next-generation-ai-inverter-compressor-in-india\" target=\"_self\">Samsung Launches Three New Refrigerators Featuring Next-Generation AI Inverter Compressor in India – Samsung Newsroom India</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Samsung 650L 4-Door Convertible French Door Refrigerator</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 650 liters.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Flexibility:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Convertible compartments for adjustable storage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>AI &amp; Smart Features:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Integrated with Samsung\'s SmartThings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Design Options:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Clean White (Glass Finish) or Black Caviar (Steel Finish) (<a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/in/samsung-launches-three-new-refrigerators-featuring-next-generation-ai-inverter-compressor-in-india\" target=\"_self\">Samsung Launches Three New Refrigerators Featuring Next-Generation AI Inverter Compressor in India – Samsung Newsroom India</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Other Notable Features Across the Lineup</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dual Ice Maker with Ice Bites:</strong> Produces up to 38 pounds of ice daily.</li>\r\n<li><strong>W