(9, 1, 1, 6, 'Hp Pavilion', 'HP Pavilion laptops are designed for everyday computing, offering a balance of performance and affordability. 1  They typically feature Intel Core or AMD Ryzen processors, integrated or dedicated graphics, and a range of storage options including SSDs and HDDs. 2  Display sizes vary, often with Full HD resolutions, and they include standard connectivity features like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and USB ports. 1  Pavilion laptops cater to general use, multimedia consumption, and light productivity tasks, with varying configurations to meet different user needs.', '<p>The <strong>HP Pavilion</strong> series offers a range of laptops with different configurations suited for productivity, entertainment, and general use. Here are the full specifications for some of the <strong>latest HP Pavilion models in 2024</strong>:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>HP Pavilion Plus 14 (2024)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Processor Options</strong>: Intel Core Ultra 5 125H, Intel Core Ultra 7 155H</li>\r\n<li><strong>Graphics</strong>: Intel Arc Graphics (7-Core), Iris Xe Graphics</li>\r\n<li><strong>RAM</strong>: Up to 16GB DDR5</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage</strong>: 512GB SSD (expandable)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Display</strong>: 14-inch OLED or IPS, Full HD or 2.8K resolution</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: 1.44 kg (3.18 lbs)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life</strong>: Estimated 8-12 hours, HP Fast Charge support</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ports</strong>: USB-C, USB-A, HDMI, headphone jack, SD card slot</li>\r\n<li><strong>Operating System</strong>: Windows 11 Home</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>HP Pavilion 15-eh3047nr</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Processor</strong>: AMD Ryzen 7</li>\r\n<li><strong>Graphics</strong>: AMD Radeon</li>\r\n<li><strong>RAM</strong>: 16GB</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage</strong>: 512GB SSD</li>\r\n<li><strong>Display</strong>: 15.6-inch Full HD</li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life</strong>: Estimated 8-10 hours</li>\r\n<li><strong>Operating System</strong>: Windows 11 Home</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>HP Pavilion x360 14\" (Convertible)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Processor Options</strong>: Intel Core i5/i7 13th Gen</li>\r\n<li><strong>Display</strong>: 14-inch Full HD Touchscreen</li>\r\n<li><strong>RAM</strong>: 8GB/16GB DDR4</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage</strong>: 256GB/512GB SSD</li>\r\n<li><strong>Graphics</strong>: Intel Iris Xe</li>\r\n<li><strong>Features</strong>: 360-degree hinge, stylus support</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ports</strong>: USB-C, USB-A, HDMI, microSD card reader</li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life</strong>: Up to 9 hours</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>HP Pavilion laptops are known for <strong>solid performance, affordability, and a mix of entertainment and productivity features</strong>. The Pavilion Plus models are designed for <strong>higher-end performance with OLED displays</strong>, while the Pavilion 15 series balances price and performance for students and professionals (<a href=\"https://www.hp.com/us-en/laptops-and-2-in-1s/pavilion.html\" target=\"_self\">HP Pavilion Laptops and 2-in-1 PCs  | HP® Official Site</a>) (<a href=\"https://laptopdecision.com/compare/hp-pavilion-plus-14-2024-vs-HP-Pavilion-15\" target=\"_self\">HP Pavilion Plus 14 2024 vs HP Pavilion 15 Laptops Detailed Comparison </a>) (<a href=\"https://www.hp.com/us-en/shop/tech-takes/hp-pavilion-15-review\" target=\"_self\">HP Pavilion 15 Review 2024: Best Value Laptop for Students &amp; Professionals | HP® Tech Takes</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Would you like help finding specific Pavilion models based on your needs?</p>\r\n', 6800, '10008', 'Active'),
(10, 1, 3, 1, 'Iphone 13 Pro Max', 'The iPhone 13 Pro Max features a 6.7-inch Super Retina XDR display with ProMotion for adaptive refresh rates up to 120Hz, powered by the A15 Bionic chip for high performance and efficiency. 1  It boasts a triple-lens rear camera system with 12MP wide, ultra-wide, and telephoto lenses, enhanced by sensor-shift optical image stabilization and Cinematic mode for video recording. 1  It offers 5G connectivity, improved battery life compared to previous models, and a durable design with Ceramic Shield front cover and IP68 water resistance.', '<p>Here are the full detailed specifications for the <strong>iPhone 13 Pro Max</strong>:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Design &amp; Build</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dimensions:</strong> 160.8 x 78.1 x 7.7 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 240g</li>\r\n<li><strong>Build:</strong> Glass front and back (Ceramic Shield), stainless steel frame</li>\r\n<li><strong>SIM:</strong> Nano-SIM and/or eSIM, Dual SIM support</li>\r\n<li><strong>Water Resistance:</strong> IP68 (up to 6m for 30 minutes)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Display</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Type:</strong> 6.7-inch Super Retina XDR OLED</li>\r\n<li><strong>Resolution:</strong> 2778 x 1284 pixels (458 PPI)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Refresh Rate:</strong> 120Hz ProMotion</li>\r\n<li><strong>HDR Support:</strong> HDR10, Dolby Vision</li>\r\n<li><strong>Brightness:</strong> 1000 nits (HBM), 1200 nits (peak)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Protection:</strong> Ceramic Shield glass</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Performance</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Chipset:</strong> Apple A15 Bionic (5nm)</li>\r\n<li><strong>CPU:</strong> Hexa-core (2x3.23 GHz Avalanche + 4x1.82 GHz Blizzard)</li>\r\n<li><strong>GPU:</strong> Apple GPU (5-core graphics)</li>\r\n<li><strong>OS:</strong> iOS 15 (upgradable to iOS 17)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Memory &amp; Storage</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>RAM:</strong> 6GB</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage Options:</strong> 128GB, 256GB, 512GB, 1TB (NVMe)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Expandable Storage:</strong> No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Camera System</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>Rear Camera (Triple)</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>12 MP Wide:</strong> f/1.5, 26mm, Dual Pixel PDAF, Sensor-shift OIS</li>\r\n<li><strong>12 MP Telephoto:</strong> f/2.8, 77mm, 3x Optical Zoom, OIS</li>\r\n<li><strong>12 MP Ultra-wide:</strong> f/1.8, 120° field of view</li>\r\n<li><strong>LiDAR Scanner:</strong> Depth sensing for night mode and AR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Rear Camera Features:</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Zoom:</strong> 3x Optical In, 2x Optical Out, 15x Digital</li>\r\n<li><strong>Modes:</strong> Night mode, Deep Fusion, Smart HDR 4, Portrait Mode</li>\r\n<li><strong>Video:</strong> 4K @ 24/30/60fps, 1080p @ 30/60/120/240fps, ProRes, Cinematic Mode</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Front Camera (Selfie)</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>12 MP Wide:</strong> f/2.2, 23mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>SL 3D sensor:</strong> Depth/Biometric sensing</li>\r\n<li><strong>Features:</strong> HDR, Night mode, Portrait mode</li>\r\n<li><strong>Video:</strong> 4K @ 24/25/30/60fps, 1080p @ 30/60/120fps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery &amp; Charging</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 4352mAh (Li-Ion, non-removable)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wired Charging:</strong> 50% in 30 minutes with 27W adapter (not included)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wireless Charging:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>MagSafe:</strong> 15W</li>\r\n<li><strong>Qi:</strong> 7.5W</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>USB:</strong> Lightning, USB 2.0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Audio</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Loudspeaker:</strong> Stereo speakers</li>\r\n<li><strong>3.5mm Jack:</strong> No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Connectivity</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>WiFi:</strong> Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax), dual-band, hotspot</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0, A2DP, LE</li>\r\n<li><strong>GPS:</strong> A-GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, QZSS, BDS</li>\r\n<li><strong>NFC:</strong> Yes</li>\r\n<li><strong>5G &amp; LTE:</strong> Supports multiple bands for global compatibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Sensors &amp; Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Face ID:</strong> Yes (3D facial recognition)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Other Sensors:</strong> Accelerometer, Gyro, Proximity, Compass, Barometer</li>\r\n<li><strong>UWB Support:</strong> Yes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Colors &amp; Price</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Colors:</strong> Graphite, Gold, Silver, Sierra Blue, Alpine Green</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> Approx. $1100 (varies by region)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, you can check:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cellsarena.com\" target=\"_self\">Cell Arena</a> (<a href=\"https://www.cellsarena.com/phones/apple/apple-iphone-13-pro-max/specs\" target=\"_self\">Apple iPhone 13 Pro Max - Full Phone Specifications</a>)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.specsbattle.com\" target=\"_self\">Specs Battle</a> (<a href=\"https://specsbattle.com/phones/apple-apple-iphone-13-pro-max\" target=\"_self\">Apple iPhone 13 Pro Max - Full Specifications and Features</a>)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.specsinsight.com\" target=\"_self\">Specs Insight</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 17000, '10009', 'Active'),
(11, 1, 1, 1, '2022 MacBook Pro', 'The 2022 MacBook Pro, available in 13-inch, 14-inch, and 16-inch models, is powered by Apple\'s M2 or M1 Pro/Max chips, offering significant performance and efficiency improvements. It features a Liquid Retina XDR display (on 14 and 16-inch models), a 1080p FaceTime HD camera, a high-fidelity six-speaker sound system, and a variety of ports including Thunderbolt, HDMI, and an SDXC card slot. The 13 inch model kept the touch bar, where the 14 and 16 inch models do not. These laptops are designed for professional users, offering long battery life, ample storage and memory options, and macOS integration for seamless workflows', '<p>The <strong>MacBook Pro 2022</strong> (14-inch and 16-inch models) features Apple\'s <strong>M2 Pro and M2 Max</strong> chips, offering a significant boost in performance compared to the previous M1-based models. Below are the full specifications:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Display &amp; Design</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Screen Sizes</strong>: 14.2-inch and 16.2-inch</li>\r\n<li><strong>Display Type</strong>: Liquid Retina XDR Mini-LED</li>\r\n<li><strong>Resolution</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>14-inch</strong>: 3024 x 1964 pixels</li>\r\n<li><strong>16-inch</strong>: 3456 x 2234 pixels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Refresh Rate</strong>: Up to 120Hz (ProMotion)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Brightness</strong>: 1000 nits sustained, 1600 nits peak (HDR)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Color Accuracy</strong>: Wide Color (P3), True Tone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Processor (M2 Pro &amp; M2 Max)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>M2 Pro</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>10-core or 12-core CPU (8 performance cores, 4 efficiency cores)</li>\r\n<li>GPU: Up to 19 cores</li>\r\n<li><strong>Performance boost</strong>: 20% faster CPU and 30% faster GPU compared to M1 Pro</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>M2 Max</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>12-core CPU (8 performance cores, 4 efficiency cores)</li>\r\n<li>GPU: Up to 38 cores</li>\r\n<li><strong>Performance boost</strong>: 30% better GPU than M1 Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Memory &amp; Storage</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unified RAM:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>M2 Pro</strong>: 16GB or 32GB</li>\r\n<li><strong>M2 Max</strong>: 32GB, 64GB, or 96GB</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Storage Options: 512GB, 1TB, 2TB, 4TB, or 8TB SSD</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery Life</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>14-inch</strong>: Up to <strong>18 hours</strong> of movie playback</li>\r\n<li><strong>16-inch</strong>: Up to <strong>22 hours</strong> of movie playback</li>\r\n<li><strong>Charging</strong>: MagSafe 3 fast charging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Ports &amp; Connectivity</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Thunderbolt 4/USB 4 Ports</strong>: 3x</li>\r\n<li><strong>HDMI</strong>: Supports up to <strong>4K 240Hz</strong> or <strong>8K 60Hz</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>SDXC Card Slot</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>MagSafe 3 Charging Port</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>3.5mm Headphone Jack</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Wi-Fi 6E &amp; Bluetooth 5.3</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Audio &amp; Camera</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Speakers</strong>: 6-speaker system with spatial audio</li>\r\n<li><strong>Microphones</strong>: Studio-quality three-mic array</li>\r\n<li><strong>Webcam</strong>: 1080p FaceTime HD camera</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Software</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>macOS Ventura</strong> (upgradable)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Features</strong>: Stage Manager, Metal 3 graphics, ProRes hardware acceleration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Build &amp; Weight</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Material</strong>: Aluminum unibody</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>14-inch</strong>: 3.5 lbs (1.6 kg)</li>\r\n<li><strong>16-inch</strong>: 4.7 lbs (2.1 kg)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Starts at <strong>$1,999</strong> for the <strong>14-inch M2 Pro</strong> model</li>\r\n<li>High-end <strong>M2 Max with 96GB RAM and 8TB storage</strong> can reach <strong>$6,499</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This model is designed for <strong>professionals in creative fields</strong> and offers <strong>top-tier performance, display, and battery life</strong> but lacks USB-A and Face ID (<a href=\"https://www.laptopmag.com/news/macbook-pros-with-m2-pro-and-m2-max-price-release-date-specs-and-more\" target=\"_self\">MacBook Pros with M2 Pro and M2 Max: Price, release date, specs, and more | Laptop Mag</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.techspot.com/products/laptops/apple-macbook-pro-142-inch-m2-pro-mid-2022.258432/\" target=\"_self\">Apple MacBook Pro 14 - M2 Pro/Max Reviews, Pros and Cons | TechSpot</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.laptopmag.com/news/the-new-14-and-16-inch-macbook-pros-are-here-say-hello-to-m2-pro-and-m2-max-power\" target=\"_self\">The new 14 and 16-inch MacBook Pros are here — say “hello” to M2 Pro and M2 Max power | Laptop Mag</a>).</p>\r\n', 27000, '10010', 'Active'),
(12, 1, 1, 1, 'Apple Magic Mouse', 'The Apple Magic Mouse is a wireless, multi-touch mouse that features a seamless, button-less surface allowing for gesture-based navigation, including scrolling, swiping, and clicking.  1  It connects via Bluetooth, utilizes a built-in rechargeable battery, and is characterized by its sleek, low-profile design. 2  The Magic Mouse incorporates advanced sensors for precise tracking and offers customizable gesture controls through macOS settings, providing a minimalist and intuitive user experience', '<p>Here are the full specifications for the <strong>Apple Magic Mouse (USB-C) 2024</strong>:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>General Information</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Type:</strong> Wireless and Rechargeable Mouse</li>\r\n<li><strong>Multi-Touch Surface:</strong> Supports gestures like swiping and scrolling</li>\r\n<li><strong>Color Options:</strong> White, Black</li>\r\n<li><strong>Optimized Foot Design:</strong> Allows smooth gliding across surfaces</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery &amp; Charging</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life:</strong> Approximately 1 month or more per charge</li>\r\n<li><strong>Charging Port:</strong> USB-C</li>\r\n<li><strong>Charging Cable Included:</strong> Woven USB-C to USB-C cable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Connectivity &amp; Compatibility</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Wireless Technology:</strong> Bluetooth</li>\r\n<li><strong>System Requirements:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mac with <strong>macOS 15.1 or later</strong></li>\r\n<li>iPad with <strong>iPadOS 18.1 or later</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Compatible Devices:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Mac Models:</strong> MacBook Air (M3, M2, M1), MacBook Pro (M3, M2, M1), iMac, Mac mini, Mac Studio, Mac Pro</li>\r\n<li><strong>iPad Models:</strong> iPad Pro (M4, 6th gen), iPad Air (M2, 5th gen), iPad Mini (A17 Pro, 6th gen)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Size &amp; Weight</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Height:</strong> 2.16 cm (0.85 inches)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Width:</strong> 5.71 cm (2.25 inches)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Depth:</strong> 11.35 cm (4.47 inches)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 0.099 kg (0.22 lbs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Additional Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Automatic Pairing with Mac</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Gesture Support for Easy Navigation</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>One-Year Manufacturer Warranty</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Made in China</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, you can check out the official Apple support page <a href=\"https://support.apple.com\" target=\"_self\">here</a> (<a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-my/121931\" target=\"_self\">Magic Mouse (USB‑C) - Tech Specs – Apple Support (MY)</a>) and purchase details at <a href=\"https://www.reliancedigital.in\" target=\"_self\">Reliance Digital</a> (<a href=\"https://www.reliancedigital.in/product/apple-magic-mouse-multitouch-surface-2024-white-m2vm3p-8697773\" target=\"_self\">Buy Apple Magic Mouse MultiTouch Surface 2024, White at Reliance Digital</a>).</p>\r\n', 900, '10011', 'Active');
