(13, 1, 8, 5, 'Music Mixer Console', 'A music mixer console, or mixing desk, is a device designed to combine, process, and route audio signals from various sources, featuring multiple input channels with gain, equalization (EQ), and panning controls, as well as auxiliary sends for effects processing and monitor mixes. Master faders control the overall output level, and many consoles include built-in preamplifiers, metering, and headphone outputs for monitoring. Digital mixers often incorporate advanced features such as digital signal processing (DSP), automation, and USB connectivity for computer integration, while analog mixers provide a more tactile and traditional workflow.', '<p>A <strong>music mixer console</strong> is an essential tool for audio production, live sound, and broadcasting. Here’s a detailed overview of the features and specifications of various mixer types available in 2024:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Types of Mixer Consoles</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>USB Mixers</strong> – Ideal for home studios and podcasting, these mixers allow direct connectivity with computers for easy recording.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Mackie ProFX8v2</li>\r\n<li>Features: Built-in effects, multiple inputs, easy-to-use interface</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Podcasters, home studio musicians  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Rackmount Mixers</strong> – Compact mixers designed for permanent installations.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Allen &amp; Heath ZEDi-10FX</li>\r\n<li>Features: High-quality preamps, space-saving design, multiple input/output options</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Small venues, churches  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Field Mixers</strong> – Portable and rugged for on-location recording in film and broadcast environments.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Sound Devices MixPre-3 II</li>\r\n<li>Features: High-quality preamps, timecode capabilities, durable design</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Filmmakers, sound engineers  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Digital Mixers</strong> – Feature-rich with remote control capabilities and built-in effects.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: TASCAM Model 2400</li>\r\n<li>Features: 24-track recorder, 24-in/22-out USB interface, DAW control, onboard EQ/compression, phantom power</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Studio recording, live performances  (<a href=\"https://futuremusic.com/2024/07/tascam-announces-model-2400-studio-live-recorder-and-mixing-console/\" target=\"_self\">TASCAM Announces Model 2400 Studio / Live Recorder and Mixing Console &lt; FutureMusic the latest news on future music technology DJ gear producing dance music edm and everything electronic</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Key Features to Look for in a Music Mixer Console</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Input Channels</strong> – The number of microphones and instruments the mixer can handle at once. Options range from compact models with 3-4 inputs to large consoles with 24+ inputs  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Preamps</strong> – High-quality preamps are crucial for clear sound. Low noise and high headroom ensure accurate audio capture  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>EQ and Effects</strong> – Built-in equalization and effects (reverb, delay, compression) enhance audio processing  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Auxiliary Sends</strong> – Allow for custom monitor mixes, essential for live performances  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>USB/DAW Integration</strong> – Many modern mixers support direct connection to Digital Audio Workstations (DAWs) for recording  (<a href=\"https://futuremusic.com/2024/07/tascam-announces-model-2400-studio-live-recorder-and-mixing-console/\" target=\"_self\">TASCAM Announces Model 2400 Studio / Live Recorder and Mixing Console &lt; FutureMusic the latest news on future music technology DJ gear producing dance music edm and everything electronic</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Analog vs. Digital</strong> – Analog mixers provide tactile control, while digital mixers offer recallable settings and advanced features  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Popular Models</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Zoom L-8</strong> – Portable, best for podcasting, features programmable sound pads  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Yamaha MG10XU</strong> – All-in-one USB mixer with built-in effects and phantom power  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Mackie ProFX4 v2</strong> – Compact mixer with USB connectivity and ReadyFX effects  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Would you like recommendations based on your specific needs (home studio, live performance, DJing, etc.)?</p>\r\n', 4500, '10012', 'Active'),
(14, 1, 5, 7, 'Nike Running Shoes', 'Nike running shoes are designed for diverse running needs, featuring lightweight, breathable uppers made from materials like engineered mesh or Flyknit, and cushioned midsoles using technologies like React, ZoomX, or Air Max for impact absorption and energy return. 1  Outsoles provide varying levels of traction and durability based on intended terrain, with models ranging from minimalist racing flats to highly supportive stability shoes. Nike running shoes also incorporate features like Flywire cables for a secure fit, and reflective elements for visibility, all tailored to enhance performance and comfort during runs', '<p>Here are the detailed specifications for some of the latest Nike running shoes in 2024:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Nike Vaporfly 3</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: 6.7 oz (190g)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cushioning</strong>: ZoomX foam with a full-length carbon fiber plate</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heel-to-Toe Drop</strong>: 8 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Performance</strong>: Known for being lightweight, highly responsive, and energy-efficient for races</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pros</strong>: Exceptionally breathable, plush cushioning, outstanding speed and efficiency</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cons</strong>: Narrow heel, not ideal for daily running</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price</strong>: Around $250  (<a href=\"https://runrepeat.com/guides/best-nike-running-shoes\" target=\"_self\">7 Best Nike Running Shoes | RunRepeat</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/best-nike-running-shoes\" target=\"_self\">8 Best Nike Running Shoes in 2024, Tested by Editors | GQ</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Nike Alphafly 3 (Best Marathon Shoe)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: ~7.5 oz</li>\r\n<li><strong>Midsole</strong>: ZoomX cushioning with Air Zoom pods</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heel-to-Toe Drop</strong>: 8 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Performance</strong>: Ideal for long-distance running and breaking personal bests</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pros</strong>: Enhanced speed, superior cushioning, excellent energy return</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cons</strong>: Expensive</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price</strong>: Around $260  (<a href=\"https://runrepeat.com/guides/best-nike-running-shoes\" target=\"_self\">7 Best Nike Running Shoes | RunRepeat</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Nike Pegasus Trail 5 (Best Road-to-Trail Running Shoe)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: 10.58 oz</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heel-to-Toe Drop</strong>: 9.5 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Use</strong>: Suitable for both road and trail running</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pros</strong>: Soft ride, versatile across multiple surfaces</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cons</strong>: Shallow lugs may not be ideal for technical trails</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price</strong>: Around $150  (<a href=\"https://www.runnea.co.uk/articles/running-news/nike-running-shoes-trail-running-15575/\" target=\"_self\">Nike s new running shoes and trail running shoes in 2024 </a>) (<a href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/best-nike-running-shoes\" target=\"_self\">8 Best Nike Running Shoes in 2024, Tested by Editors | GQ</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Nike Pegasus 41 GORE-TEX (Best Waterproof Running Shoe)</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: 10.4 oz</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heel-to-Toe Drop</strong>: 10 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Waterproofing</strong>: GORE-TEX technology for all-weather running</li>\r\n<li><strong>Performance</strong>: Comfortable and bouncy ride, snug fit</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pros</strong>: Effective waterproofing, solid grip, good for all weather conditions</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cons</strong>: Slightly stiffer than the regular Pegasus</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price</strong>: Around $160  (<a href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/best-nike-running-shoes\" target=\"_self\">8 Best Nike Running Shoes in 2024, Tested by Editors | GQ</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These models represent some of the best Nike running shoes available in 2024, each designed for different types of runners and conditions. Let me know if you need a comparison or a recommendation based on your specific needs!</p>\r\n', 500, '10013', 'Active'),
(15, 1, 5, 7, 'Nike Air Force 1', 'Nike Air Force 1 shoes are low, mid, or high-top basketball-inspired sneakers featuring a leather or synthetic upper, a perforated toe box for ventilation, and a durable rubber sole with Nike Air cushioning for impact absorption. 1  They are recognized by their distinct silhouette, including a thick midsole and a prominent side Swoosh logo, and are available in a wide range of colors and materials, catering to both athletic performance and casual streetwear fashion.', '<p>A <strong>music mixer console</strong> is an essential tool for audio production, live sound, and broadcasting. Here’s a detailed overview of the features and specifications of various mixer types available in 2024:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Types of Mixer Consoles</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>USB Mixers</strong> – Ideal for home studios and podcasting, these mixers allow direct connectivity with computers for easy recording.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Mackie ProFX8v2</li>\r\n<li>Features: Built-in effects, multiple inputs, easy-to-use interface</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Podcasters, home studio musicians  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Rackmount Mixers</strong> – Compact mixers designed for permanent installations.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Allen &amp; Heath ZEDi-10FX</li>\r\n<li>Features: High-quality preamps, space-saving design, multiple input/output options</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Small venues, churches  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Field Mixers</strong> – Portable and rugged for on-location recording in film and broadcast environments.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: Sound Devices MixPre-3 II</li>\r\n<li>Features: High-quality preamps, timecode capabilities, durable design</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Filmmakers, sound engineers  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Digital Mixers</strong> – Feature-rich with remote control capabilities and built-in effects.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Example: TASCAM Model 2400</li>\r\n<li>Features: 24-track recorder, 24-in/22-out USB interface, DAW control, onboard EQ/compression, phantom power</li>\r\n<li>Best for: Studio recording, live performances  (<a href=\"https://futuremusic.com/2024/07/tascam-announces-model-2400-studio-live-recorder-and-mixing-console/\" target=\"_self\">TASCAM Announces Model 2400 Studio / Live Recorder and Mixing Console &lt; FutureMusic the latest news on future music technology DJ gear producing dance music edm and everything electronic</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Key Features to Look for in a Music Mixer Console</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Input Channels</strong> – The number of microphones and instruments the mixer can handle at once. Options range from compact models with 3-4 inputs to large consoles with 24+ inputs  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Preamps</strong> – High-quality preamps are crucial for clear sound. Low noise and high headroom ensure accurate audio capture  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>EQ and Effects</strong> – Built-in equalization and effects (reverb, delay, compression) enhance audio processing  (<a href=\"https://prosoundnation.com/mastering-the-mix-the-definitive-2024-guide-to-audio-mixer-functionality-and-innovative-features/\" target=\"_self\">Mastering the Mix: The Definitive 2024 Guide to Audio Mixers Functionality and Features – ProSoundNatioan</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Auxiliary Sends</strong> – Allow for custom monitor mixes, essential for live performances  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>USB/DAW Integration</strong> – Many modern mixers support direct connection to Digital Audio Workstations (DAWs) for recording  (<a href=\"https://futuremusic.com/2024/07/tascam-announces-model-2400-studio-live-recorder-and-mixing-console/\" target=\"_self\">TASCAM Announces Model 2400 Studio / Live Recorder and Mixing Console &lt; FutureMusic the latest news on future music technology DJ gear producing dance music edm and everything electronic</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Analog vs. Digital</strong> – Analog mixers provide tactile control, while digital mixers offer recallable settings and advanced features  (<a href=\"https://equipboard.com/posts/best-audio-mixers\" target=\"_self\">Best Audio Mixers Comparison: Top 10 Picks for Every Budget 2025 | Equipboard</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Popular Models</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Zoom L-8</strong> – Portable, best for podcasting, features programmable sound pads  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Yamaha MG10XU</strong> – All-in-one USB mixer with built-in effects and phantom power  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Mackie ProFX4 v2</strong> – Compact mixer with USB connectivity and ReadyFX effects  (<a href=\"https://www.soundswow.com/best-mixing-console-for-home-studio/\" target=\"_self\">9 Best Mixing Consoles for Home Studio in 2025</a>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Would you like recommendations based on your specific needs (home studio, live performance, DJing, etc.)?</p>\r\n', 1000, '10014', 'Active'),
(16, 1, 5, 7, 'Official Leather Shoes', 'Official leather shoes, designed for formal or professional settings, are typically crafted from high-quality leather, featuring a polished finish and a closed lacing system like Oxford or Derby styles, or a slip-on design such as loafers. They prioritize a sleek, refined silhouette with a low, stacked heel and a durable leather or rubber sole, ensuring both comfort and a sophisticated appearance. Construction emphasizes durability and longevity, often incorporating features like Goodyear welting, and a smooth, comfortable lining.', '<p>Here are the full specifications for official leather shoes, including materials, features, and advantages:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Material Types</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Full Grain Leather</strong>: The highest quality leather, durable, breathable, and develops a rich patina over time.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Top Grain Leather</strong>: Slightly lower in quality than full grain but still durable; often treated for a smoother finish.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Genuine Leather</strong>: Lower in quality, made from the inner layers of the hide with a processed surface.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Patent Leather</strong>: Coated with a glossy finish for a sleek, formal look.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Features of Official Leather Shoes</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Construction</strong>: Handcrafted or machine-made using techniques such as Goodyear welt, Blake stitch, or cemented sole construction.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sole Material</strong>: Leather, rubber, or a combination for durability and comfort.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lining</strong>: Leather or fabric for moisture absorption and breathability.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Toe Styles</strong>: Options like round, square, pointed, or cap-toe designs.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Closure Types</strong>: Laces, buckles (Monk straps), slip-on (Loafers), or elastic side panels (Chelsea boots).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Insole</strong>: Cushioned for added comfort.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heel Type</strong>: Varies from flat to stacked or heeled for different levels of formality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Advantages of Leather Shoes</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Durability</strong>: High-quality leather shoes can last for years if maintained properly.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Breathability</strong>: Natural leather allows air circulation, preventing sweat buildup.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Aesthetic Appeal</strong>: Leather shoes enhance both formal and casual looks.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Comfort</strong>: Over time, leather molds to the shape of your feet, providing a custom fit.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Versatility</strong>: Available in various styles suitable for business, casual, or formal wear.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Maintenance Tips</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cleaning</strong>: Use a damp cloth and leather cleaner to remove dirt.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Conditioning</strong>: Apply leather conditioner to prevent drying and cracking.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Polishing</strong>: Regular polishing maintains shine and protects the leather.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage</strong>: Keep in a cool, dry place with shoe trees to maintain shape.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1400, '10014', 'Active'),
(17, 1, 6, 5, 'PlayStation 5 (PS5)', 'The PlayStation 5 (PS5) is a ninth-generation home video game console featuring a custom AMD Zen 2 CPU and RDNA 2-based GPU, supporting 4K resolution at 120 frames per second with ray tracing capabilities. It utilizes a custom high-speed SSD for significantly faster loading times, and the DualSense controller introduces haptic feedback and adaptive triggers for enhanced immersion. The console offers backwards compatibility with most PS4 games and comes in two models: a standard version with an Ultra HD Blu-ray disc drive and a Digital Edition without a disc drive.', '<p>Here are the full specifications for the <strong>PlayStation 5 (PS5):</strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Hardware Specifications</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>CPU:</strong> AMD Ryzen™ “Zen 2” (8 cores, 16 threads) | Up to 3.5 GHz (Variable Frequency)</li>\r\n<li><strong>GPU:</strong> AMD Radeon™ RDNA 2 | Up to 2.23 GHz (10.3 TFLOPS) | Ray Tracing Acceleration</li>\r\n<li><strong>Memory:</strong> 16GB GDDR6 RAM | 448GB/s Bandwidth</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage:</strong> 825GB SSD | 5.5GB/s Read Bandwidth (Raw)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Optical Drive:</strong> Ultra HD Blu-ray (Supports up to 100GB discs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Performance &amp; Display</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Resolution Support:</strong> Up to 8K | 4K at 120Hz | Variable Refresh Rate (VRR) via HDMI 2.1</li>\r\n<li><strong>Game Disc Format:</strong> Ultra HD Blu-ray</li>\r\n<li><strong>Audio:</strong> “Tempest” 3D AudioTech for immersive sound</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Connectivity &amp; Ports</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>USB Ports:</strong> 1x USB Type-A (Hi-Speed), 2x USB Type-A (Super-Speed 10Gbps), 1x USB Type-C (Super-Speed 10Gbps)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Networking:</strong> Ethernet, Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax), Bluetooth 5.1</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Physical Dimensions &amp; Power</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Size:</strong> 390mm × 104mm × 260mm (Standard Edition) | 390mm × 92mm × 260mm (Digital Edition)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 4.5kg (Standard Edition) | 3.9kg (Digital Edition)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Power Consumption:</strong> 350W (Standard Edition) | 340W (Digital Edition)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>DualSense Controller Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Adaptive Triggers</strong> with haptic feedback for realistic sensations</li>\r\n<li><strong>Six-axis motion sensing</strong> (gyroscope + accelerometer)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Built-in microphone and speaker</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>USB-C charging</strong> and <strong>3.5mm headphone jack</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life:</strong> Improved over DualShock 4</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Additional Accessories &amp; Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>PS VR2 Compatibility</strong> for virtual reality gaming</li>\r\n<li><strong>PS5 Digital Edition</strong> (Same specs but lacks a disc drive)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Backward Compatibility:</strong> Supports most PS4 games</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, visit <a href=\"https://www.psu.com\" target=\"_self\">PlayStation Universe</a> and <a href=\"https://www.bestbuy.com\" target=\"_self\">Best Buy</a> (<a href=\"https://www.psu.com/news/sony-ps5-release-date-price-faq-specs-psvr2-backwards-compatibility/\" target=\"_self\">Sony PS5 Complete Guide - Everything Explained About PlayStation 5 For New Owners In 2024 - PlayStation Universe</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.bestbuy.com/site/video-games/playstation-5/pcmcat1572034351415.c?id=pcmcat1572034351415\" target=\"_self\">Sony PlayStation 5: PS5 - Best Buy</a>).</p>\r\n', 8900, '10015', 'Active'),
(18, 1, 1, 3, 'Samsung Smart TV', 'Samsung Smart TVs range from entry-level HD to high-end 8K models, utilizing LED, QLED, or Neo QLED display technologies for vibrant colors and sharp images, and are powered by the Tizen operating system for access to streaming apps and smart home integration. 1  They typically feature multiple HDMI and USB ports, built-in Wi-Fi and Bluetooth connectivity, and voice control capabilities through Bixby or compatibility with other virtual assistants. 2 ', '<h3><strong>Samsung Smart TV 2024 - Full Specifications and Details</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Samsung’s 2024 Smart TV lineup includes a variety of models featuring <strong>OLED, QLED, Neo QLED, and 8K technology</strong>. Below is a breakdown of the key specifications and features:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>1. Display Technology</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>OLED TVs (S90D, S95D)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Uses <strong>QD-OLED</strong> panels for improved brightness and color accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Features <strong>OLED Glare-Free technology</strong> (S95D) for better viewing in bright environments.</li>\r\n<li><strong>144Hz refresh rate</strong> for smooth gaming performance.</li>\r\n<li>Supports <strong>HDR10+, HLG</strong> for high dynamic range content.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Neo QLED TVs (QN900D, QN800D, QN95D, QN90D, QN85D)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Uses <strong>Mini LED backlighting</strong> for better contrast and local dimming.</li>\r\n<li>Supports <strong>8K (QN900D, QN800D) and 4K (QN95D, QN90D, QN85D) resolutions</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Features <strong>Quantum HDR</strong> for superior brightness and color depth.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>QLED TVs (Q80D, Q70D, Q60D)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Quantum Dot technology</strong> for enhanced color reproduction.</li>\r\n<li>Available in <strong>4K UHD resolution</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Supports <strong>Direct Full Array</strong> backlighting for improved contrast.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Crystal UHD TVs</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Entry-level 4K models with <strong>PurColor technology</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Edge-lit LED panels with <strong>Auto Motion Plus</strong> for smoother motion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Smart Features &amp; Software</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Powered by <strong>Tizen OS 2024</strong> with:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Personalized User Profiles</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Built-in <strong>Samsung Gaming Hub</strong> (supports Xbox Cloud Gaming, Nvidia GeForce Now).</li>\r\n<li><strong>AI-powered Smart Calibration</strong> for picture adjustments.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Samsung Knox Security</strong> for privacy protection.</li>\r\n<li>Access to <strong>Samsung TV Plus</strong> (free streaming channels).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Audio &amp; Sound System</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Object Tracking Sound+ (OTS+)</strong> with <strong>Dolby Atmos</strong> support.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Adaptive Sound+</strong> enhances audio based on room acoustics.</li>\r\n<li>Select models feature <strong>built-in subwoofers</strong> for better bass performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>4. Connectivity &amp; Ports</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>HDMI 2.1 (up to 4 ports)</strong> for 4K 120Hz gaming.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wi-Fi 6E &amp; Bluetooth 5.2</strong> for faster wireless connections.</li>\r\n<li><strong>USB 3.0 &amp; Ethernet ports</strong> for wired connectivity.</li>\r\n<li><strong>eARC support</strong> for high-fidelity audio passthrough.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Additional Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>One Connect Box</strong> (available on select models) for cleaner cable management.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Slim, Bezel-less Design</strong> with ultra-thin profiles.</li>\r\n<li><strong>AI-powered 4K &amp; 8K upscaling</strong> for better image quality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Samsung Lifestyle TVs</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>The Frame (LS03D)</strong>: Customizable design that displays artwork when not in use.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The Serif &amp; The Sero</strong>: Unique form factors designed for aesthetics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 15000, '10015', 'Active'),
(19, 1, 1, 3, 'Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra', 'The Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra boasts a titanium frame, a 6.8-inch Dynamic AMOLED 2X display with a 120Hz adaptive refresh rate, and is powered by the Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 for Galaxy processor. 1  It features a quad rear camera setup, including a 200MP main sensor, a 12MP ultra-wide lens, a 10MP telephoto lens with 3x optical zoom, and a 50MP telephoto lens with 5x optical zoom, alongside a 12MP front-facing camera.', '<p>The <strong>Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra</strong> comes with high-end specifications, making it one of the most powerful smartphones of 2024. Here are the full details:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Display</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Size:</strong> 6.8 inches, Dynamic AMOLED 2X</li>\r\n<li><strong>Resolution:</strong> 1440 x 3088 pixels (QHD+)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Refresh Rate:</strong> 1-120Hz Adaptive Refresh Rate</li>\r\n<li><strong>Brightness:</strong> 2600 nits peak brightness</li>\r\n<li><strong>Protection:</strong> Corning Gorilla Glass Armor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Performance</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Chipset:</strong> Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 (4 nm)</li>\r\n<li><strong>CPU:</strong> Octa-core (1x3.39 GHz Cortex-X4 &amp; 5x3.15 GHz Cortex-A720 &amp; 2x2.27 GHz Cortex-A520)</li>\r\n<li><strong>GPU:</strong> Adreno 750</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Memory &amp; Storage</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>RAM:</strong> 12GB</li>\r\n<li><strong>Storage Options:</strong> 256GB, 512GB, 1TB (UFS 4.0)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Expandable Storage:</strong> No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Camera System</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>Rear Cameras: Quad Setup</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Main Sensor:</strong> 200 MP, f/1.7, OIS</li>\r\n<li><strong>Telephoto:</strong> 10 MP, f/2.4, 3x optical zoom</li>\r\n<li><strong>Periscope Telephoto:</strong> 50 MP, f/3.4, 5x optical zoom</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ultrawide:</strong> 12 MP, f/2.2, 120˚ field of view</li>\r\n<li><strong>Video Recording:</strong> 8K at 24/30fps, 4K at 30/60/120fps, 1080p at 30/60/240fps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Front Camera</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Resolution:</strong> 12 MP, f/2.2</li>\r\n<li><strong>Features:</strong> Dual Pixel PDAF, 4K at 30/60fps, 1080p at 30fps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery &amp; Charging</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 5000 mAh</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wired Charging:</strong> 45W fast charging (65% in 30 minutes)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wireless Charging:</strong> 15W (Qi/PMA)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Reverse Wireless Charging:</strong> 4.5W</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Software &amp; Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Operating System:</strong> Android 14 with One UI 6.1</li>\r\n<li><strong>Software Updates:</strong> 7 years of OS &amp; security updates</li>\r\n<li><strong>AI Features:</strong> Live Translate, Note Assist, Generative Edit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Connectivity &amp; Other Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>SIM:</strong> Dual SIM (Nano-SIM &amp; eSIM)</li>\r\n<li><strong>5G:</strong> Yes, NSA/SA</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wi-Fi:</strong> Wi-Fi 7, Wi-Fi 6E</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.3</li>\r\n<li><strong>USB:</strong> USB Type-C 3.2</li>\r\n<li><strong>NFC:</strong> Yes</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> Ultrasonic Fingerprint Scanner (under-display), Face Unlock</li>\r\n<li><strong>Stylus:</strong> Built-in S Pen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Build &amp; Design</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Frame:</strong> Titanium</li>\r\n<li><strong>Water &amp; Dust Resistance:</strong> IP68 (up to 1.5m for 30 min)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 232g</li>\r\n<li><strong>Colors:</strong> Titanium Black, Titanium Gray, Titanium Violet, Titanium Yellow</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Price &amp; Availability</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Release Date:</strong> January 2024</li>\r\n<li><strong>Price:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>12GB/256GB:</strong> ~$999.60</li>\r\n<li><strong>12GB/512GB:</strong> ~$1,324.97</li>\r\n<li><strong>12GB/1TB:</strong> Varies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, you can check <strong>Samsung\'s official website</strong> or sources like <strong>MobilityArena</strong> and <strong>SamMobile</strong>  (<a href=\"https://mobilityarena.com/samsung-galaxy-s24-ultra-full-phone-specs/\" target=\"_self\">Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra: Full phone specifications (US) - MobilityArena</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.sammobile.com/samsung/galaxy-s24-ultra/specs/\" target=\"_self\">Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra full device specifications - SamMobile</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.samsung.com/uk/smartphones/galaxy-s24-ultra/specs/\" target=\"_self\">Specs | Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra | Samsung UK</a>).</p>\r\n', 19000, '10016', 'Active'),
(20, 1, 8, 5, ' Sony Speakers', 'Sony speakers encompass a broad spectrum, from portable Bluetooth models to high-fidelity home theater systems, characterized by their diverse audio technologies and design aesthetics. They often feature proprietary drivers and sound processing algorithms like Extra Bass or ClearAudio+ to enhance sound clarity and depth, while also incorporating features like wireless connectivity, water resistance (in portable models), and multi-room audio capabilities. 1  Sony\'s range includes soundbars, bookshelf speakers, and subwoofers, aiming to provide a comprehensive audio experience with varying levels of sophistication and power output.', '<p>Here are the full specifications for the <strong>Sony SRS-XP700 X-Series Portable Wireless Speaker</strong>:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Sound</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Speaker Size</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Front Tweeters: 6 cm × 3</li>\r\n<li>Rear Tweeter: 5 cm × 1</li>\r\n<li>Woofers: 17 cm × 2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Sound Modes</strong>: Clear Audio+, DSEE, LIVE SOUND, Omnidirectional Party Sound</li>\r\n<li><strong>Mega Bass</strong>: Enhanced bass feature for deeper sound</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Size &amp; Weight</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dimensions</strong>: 313 mm × 693 mm × 367 mm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight</strong>: 16.9 kg</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery &amp; Power</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Life</strong>: Up to 25 hours</li>\r\n<li><strong>Charging</strong>: Quick Charge (10 minutes charge = 3 hours playtime)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Care Feature</strong>: Protects battery from overcharging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Bluetooth &amp; Connectivity</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Supported Codecs</strong>: SBC, AAC, LDAC</li>\r\n<li><strong>Inputs</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stereo Mini Jack (IN)</li>\r\n<li>USB-A</li>\r\n<li>Microphone Input (6.3mm)</li>\r\n<li>Guitar Input (6.3mm)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>USB Charging</strong>: Can charge other devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Durability</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Water Resistance</strong>: IPX4 (splash-proof)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Special Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Live Sound Mode</strong>: Simulates live music experience</li>\r\n<li><strong>Omnidirectional Party Sound</strong>: Full-range audio for all directions</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lighting Effects</strong>: Multiple ambient lighting patterns</li>\r\n<li><strong>Party Connect</strong>: Sync up to 100 speakers</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sony | Music Center App</strong>: Controls audio, lighting, and settings via smartphone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Portability &amp; Design</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Flexible Placement</strong>: Can be used upright or on its side</li>\r\n<li><strong>Carrying Handle</strong>: Easy to transport</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, you can visit <a href=\"https://www.sony-asia.com\" target=\"_self\">Sony’s official website</a> (<a href=\"https://www.sony-asia.com/electronics/wireless-speakers/srs-xp700/specifications\" target=\"_self\">SRS-XP700 Specifications | All Wireless Speakers | Sony Asia Pacific</a>). Let me know if you need help comparing models!</p>\r\n', 16000, '10016', 'Active'),
(21, 1, 10, 2, 'Starlink Internet Kit', 'The Starlink Internet Kit provides satellite-based internet access through a user terminal (dishy) and Wi-Fi router, designed for areas with limited terrestrial connectivity. 1  It includes a self-orienting phased-array antenna that connects to a network of low-Earth orbit satellites, a power supply, and cabling. 2  The system aims for high-speed, low-latency internet, though performance can vary based on weather conditions and satellite coverage. 3  Installation involves mounting the dish with a clear view of the sky and connecting the provided router for Wi-Fi access', '<p>The <strong>Starlink Internet Kit</strong> consists of a user terminal (dish), a Wi-Fi router, a power supply, and a mounting tripod. It enables satellite-based internet connectivity, primarily designed for areas with limited or no access to traditional broadband services.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Key Specifications:</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Download Speeds:</strong> Typically between <strong>25 to 220 Mbps</strong>, with most users experiencing speeds over <strong>100 Mbps</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Upload Speeds:</strong> Generally <strong>5 to 20 Mbps</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Latency:</strong> Ranges between <strong>25 to 60 ms</strong> on land and <strong>100+ ms</strong> in remote locations (e.g., oceans, islands, polar regions).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Service Plans:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Standard (Fixed):</strong> 25-100 Mbps download, 5-10 Mbps upload, 25-60 ms latency.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Priority (Fixed):</strong> 40-220 Mbps download, 8-25 Mbps upload, 25-60 ms latency.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Mobile (Mobility):</strong> 5-50 Mbps download, 2-10 Mbps upload, &lt;99 ms latency.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Mobile Priority (Mobility):</strong> 40-220 Mbps download, 8-25 Mbps upload, &lt;99 ms latency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Hardware &amp; Connectivity:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The dish requires a <strong>clear view of the sky</strong> to function optimally.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wi-Fi Router:</strong> Supports dual-band Wi-Fi for indoor connectivity.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Power Usage:</strong> Varies by kit version, typically <strong>50-100W</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Can be powered by <strong>AC mains or DC with an adapter</strong> for mobile applications.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Durability:</strong> Designed to last <strong>12 to 24 months</strong> if properly maintained.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Firmware Updates:</strong> Automatic updates from SpaceX to improve performance.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Interference Sensitivity:</strong> Performance can be affected by obstacles, extreme weather, and network congestion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more detailed information, visit Starlink’s official specifications page: <a href=\"https://www.starlink.com/legal/documents/DOC-1400-28829-70\" target=\"_self\">Starlink Official Site</a> (<a href=\"https://www.starlink.com/legal/documents/DOC-1400-28829-70\" target=\"_self\">Starlink Specifications - Starlink</a>).</p>\r\n', 8000, '10017', 'Active'),
(22, 1, 9, 7, 'Janet Suits', 'A suit typically comprises a jacket and trousers made from matching fabric, designed for formal or semi-formal occasions. The jacket, structured with padded shoulders and a tailored waist, features lapels, buttons, and pockets, while the trousers are creased and designed to drape smoothly. Suit fabrics range from wool and linen to synthetic blends, with variations in weave, weight, and pattern. Fit is crucial, with attention to shoulder width, chest circumference, sleeve length, and trouser waist and inseam. Quality suits exhibit meticulous stitching, durable linings, and well-constructed buttonholes, reflecting craftsmanship and longevity.', '<p>A <strong>suit</strong> is a formal ensemble consisting of a jacket and matching trousers (or skirt for women), typically made from the same fabric. Here are the full specifications of a high-quality suit:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>1. Fabric &amp; Material</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Common Materials:</strong> Wool, Cotton, Linen, Polyester, Silk, Velvet, Tweed, Cashmere</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weave Types:</strong> Twill, Herringbone, Houndstooth, Sharkskin, Flannel</li>\r\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lightweight (150-250 g/m²) – suitable for summer</li>\r\n<li>Medium weight (250-350 g/m²) – all-season wear</li>\r\n<li>Heavyweight (350+ g/m²) – winter suits</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Jacket Specifications</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Style:</strong> Single-Breasted (1, 2, or 3 buttons) or Double-Breasted (4, 6, or 8 buttons)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lapels:</strong> Notch, Peak, or Shawl</li>\r\n<li><strong>Fit Types:</strong> Classic, Slim, Modern, or Tailored Fit</li>\r\n<li><strong>Vent Types:</strong> Single Vent, Double Vent, No Vent</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pockets:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Outside: Flap, Jetted, Patch</li>\r\n<li>Inside: Usually 2-4 pockets for storage</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Shoulders:</strong> Soft (Unstructured) or Padded (Structured)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Buttons:</strong> Plastic, Horn, Metal, or Mother of Pearl</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lining:</strong> Fully Lined, Half Lined, or Unlined (often made of polyester, silk, or viscose)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Trousers Specifications</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Fit:</strong> Slim, Regular, or Relaxed Fit</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pleats:</strong> Flat Front, Single Pleat, or Double Pleats</li>\r\n<li><strong>Waistband:</strong> With or Without Belt Loops (can include side adjusters or suspenders)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Pockets:</strong> Side Pockets (slanted or vertical), Back Pockets (buttoned or unbuttoned)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Hem Style:</strong> Cuffed or Plain Hem</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>4. Additional Suit Elements</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Vest (Optional for 3-Piece Suit):</strong> Matching or Contrasting</li>\r\n<li><strong>Accessories:</strong> Tie, Pocket Square, Cufflinks, Lapel Pin</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Colors &amp; Patterns</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Solid Colors:</strong> Black, Navy, Gray, Charcoal, Brown, White</li>\r\n<li><strong>Patterns:</strong> Pinstripe, Checkered, Windowpane, Glen Plaid</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Would you like recommendations for specific brands or occasions (business, casual, wedding, etc.)?</p>\r\n', 3100, '10017', 'Active'),
(23, 1, 4, 2, '2024 Tesla Model S', 'Tesla \"saloon cars\" (referring to their sedan models like the Model S and Model 3) are electric vehicles characterized by their sleek, minimalist design, advanced autonomous driving capabilities (Autopilot and Full Self-Driving), and high-performance electric powertrains. 1  They feature large touchscreen displays for infotainment and vehicle controls, over-the-air software updates for continuous improvement, and long-range battery options. 1  Known for their rapid acceleration and supercharging network, Tesla sedans prioritize efficiency, technology, and a premium electric driving experience', '<p>Here are the full specifications for the <strong>2024 Tesla Model S</strong>, one of Tesla\'s premier electric sedans:</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Performance &amp; Powertrain</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Drivetrain</strong>: All-wheel drive (AWD)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Motor Configuration</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dual Motor Model S</strong>: 670 hp</li>\r\n<li><strong>Plaid Model S</strong>: 1,020 hp (Tri-Motor)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>0-60 mph Acceleration</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dual Motor Model S</strong>: ~3.1 seconds</li>\r\n<li><strong>Plaid Model S</strong>: 1.99 seconds</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Transmission</strong>: 1-speed direct drive</li>\r\n<li><strong>Top Speed</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dual Motor Model S</strong>: 149 mph</li>\r\n<li><strong>Plaid Model S</strong>: 200 mph</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Battery &amp; Charging</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Battery Capacity</strong>: Estimated ~100 kWh</li>\r\n<li><strong>EPA Estimated Range</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Dual Motor Model S</strong>: 402 miles</li>\r\n<li><strong>Plaid Model S</strong>: 359 miles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Charging Speed</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Supercharger Max Rate</strong>: 250 kW</li>\r\n<li><strong>Home Charging (240V)</strong>: ~15 hours for a full charge</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Exterior &amp; Dimensions</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Overall Length</strong>: 197.7 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Overall Width</strong>: 78.2 in. (without mirrors), 86.2 in. (with mirrors)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Height</strong>: 56.3 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wheelbase</strong>: 116.5 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Ground Clearance</strong>: 5.0 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Curb Weight</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dual Motor Model S: 4,560 lbs</li>\r\n<li>Plaid Model S: 4,776 lbs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Wheels &amp; Tires</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Standard Wheel Size</strong>: 19 inches (optional 21-inch wheels available)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tire Sizes</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Front: 255/45R19</li>\r\n<li>Rear: 285/40R19</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Wheel Type</strong>: Alloy wheels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Interior &amp; Comfort</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Seating Capacity</strong>: 5 passengers</li>\r\n<li><strong>Upholstery</strong>: Leatherette</li>\r\n<li><strong>Front Headroom</strong>: 39.7 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Front Legroom</strong>: 42.4 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rear Headroom</strong>: 38.1 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rear Legroom</strong>: 35.5 in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cargo Space</strong>: 28.1 cubic feet</li>\r\n<li><strong>Heated &amp; Ventilated Seats</strong>: Standard</li>\r\n<li><strong>Panoramic Glass Roof</strong>: Standard</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Technology &amp; Features</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Autopilot &amp; Full Self-Driving (Optional)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Adaptive Cruise Control</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Tesla Infotainment System</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>17-inch touchscreen</li>\r\n<li>Premium sound system</li>\r\n<li>Wireless gaming (with controller support)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Navigation</strong>: Standard</li>\r\n<li><strong>Keyless Entry &amp; Start</strong>: Standard</li>\r\n<li><strong>Over-the-Air (OTA) Software Updates</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Safety</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Autonomous Emergency Braking</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Collision Avoidance System</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Surround Camera System</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Lane Keeping Assist</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Adaptive Headlights</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing &amp; Ownership Costs</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Base Price</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dual Motor Model S: ~$88,490</li>\r\n<li>Plaid Model S: ~$108,490</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>5-Year Cost to Own</strong>: Estimated $97,006–$114,003</li>\r\n<li><strong>Warranty</strong>:<br></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Standard Vehicle Warranty</strong>: 4 years / 50,000 miles</li>\r\n<li><strong>Battery &amp; Drive Unit Warranty</strong>: 8 years / 150,000 miles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more details, you can check out the full specifications on <a href=\"https://www.edmunds.com\" target=\"_self\">Edmunds</a> and <a href=\"https://www.carweek.com\" target=\"_self\">CarWeek</a> (<a href=\"https://www.edmunds.com/tesla/model-s/2024/trims/\" target=\"_self\">2024 Tesla Model S Sedan Trims Comparison | Edmunds</a>) (<a href=\"https://www.carweek.com/research/tesla/model-s/2024\" target=\"_self\">2024 Tesla Model S Specs, Review, Pricing &amp; Photos</a>).</p>\r\n', 506000, '10018', 'Active');
